like this before. But I just wanna talk about

00:01:27.189 --> 00:01:30.950
how I got here, right? So, if I never wanted
to write a book, how did I get to this point

00:01:30.950 --> 00:01:36.340
where we have a book that just came out? So,
this all started a little over a year ago.

00:01:36.340 --> 00:01:42.799
The agency where Mike and I came together
and co-hosted a conference for our clients.

00:01:42.799 --> 00:01:46.490
And what we were finding is with all of the
changes and all the new technologies that

00:01:46.490 --> 00:01:51.170
were impacting television, is we were really
challenged with how to educate our clients

00:01:51.170 --> 00:01:55.100
on how these are impacting their marketing
plans. We would go out to our clients and

00:01:55.100 --> 00:01:58.980
present one technology. We'd go out and say,
"We wanna test this."

00:01:58.980 --> 00:02:02.719
But our clients didn't have these technologies.
They didn't have connected TVs in their homes.

00:02:02.719 --> 00:02:07.460
They didn't have the apps on their phones.
And so, we put this conference together a

00:02:07.460 --> 00:02:13.030
year ago to really create an opportunity for
our clients to experience what was happening

00:02:13.030 --> 00:02:18.090
with television. Erin came and spoke with
us last year on our connected TV panel.

00:02:18.090 --> 00:02:22.319
And we got a great response from our clients.
They were really excited to see what was happening.

00:02:22.319 --> 00:02:27.030
And because they were able to experience it,
they were starting to understand why they

00:02:27.030 --> 00:02:33.730
needed to take these things so seriously.
So, my background is television. And for the

00:02:33.730 --> 00:02:37.440
past several years, all I keep hearing about
is the death of TV and it drives me insane

00:02:37.440 --> 00:02:43.300
because our clients, they do spend a lot of
money in television, but we do a lot of research,

00:02:43.300 --> 00:02:49.400
a lot of multi-mix modeling, to justify the
fact that television is a very powerful medium

00:02:49.400 --> 00:02:51.660
in driving sales for our clients.

00:02:51.660 --> 00:02:57.300
And so, to hear that television is dead and
not as powerful as it once was, was very frustrating

00:02:57.300 --> 00:03:02.580
for me. But it's definitely not the same as
what it was. While people are watching more

00:03:02.580 --> 00:03:08.950
TV than ever, it's a different experience
today than it was when we were growing up.

00:03:08.950 --> 00:03:11.330
So, it's not this passive experience.

00:03:11.330 --> 00:03:16.430
And it's not even this great, high-definition,
single, big screen experience in your living

00:03:16.430 --> 00:03:23.700
room anymore. It's different. It's this converging
media, right? So, you have social media converging

00:03:23.700 --> 00:03:28.400
with television, which is creating new experiences
for viewers with their favorite television

00:03:28.400 --> 00:03:30.580
shows. So, it's much more complicated.

00:03:30.580 --> 00:03:35.099
As a television buyer, as somebody's who's
trying to find the right environment to place

00:03:35.099 --> 00:03:39.020
our client's messages so that they get through
to consumers and we get them to go in and

00:03:39.020 --> 00:03:44.450
buy our products, I can't just look at television
on the television screen anymore. I need to

00:03:44.450 --> 00:03:49.300
look at this content that's been created to
run on television, but now is available on

00:03:49.300 --> 00:03:51.580
all these different platforms.

00:03:51.580 --> 00:03:56.620
So, all these different things now come into
play. We have tablet. We have mobile. We have

00:03:56.620 --> 00:04:04.019
connected TV devices--all of these different
options for our clients to reach their customers.

00:04:04.019 --> 00:04:09.970
As you've seen, live TV is alive as ever.
If you look at--. And it's boosted by social

00:04:09.970 --> 00:04:14.159
media. So, if you just look at some of the
most recent examples, you have the Super Bowl.

00:04:14.159 --> 00:04:17.450
Highest tweets per second, the Super Bowl
peak came at the end of the game--over 12

00:04:17.450 --> 00:04:18.940
thousand tweets per second.

00:04:18.940 --> 00:04:22.770
Madonna's performance was second--over ten
thousand. So, you can see that people wanna

00:04:22.770 --> 00:04:27.350
talk about what they're watching, particularly
in a live environment. It was the most watched

00:04:27.350 --> 00:04:33.660
TV program ever. Same thing with the Grammys.
Adele, coming back from her surgery, singing

00:04:33.660 --> 00:04:34.960
for the first time.

00:04:34.960 --> 00:04:39.630
Thirteen million mentions. These are pretty
significant numbers. This isn't just a small

00:04:39.630 --> 00:04:44.190
group of people who are talking about things.
This is a pretty massive group of people that

00:04:44.190 --> 00:04:50.790
we need to pay attention to. And their influence
on other people is pretty important. So, the

00:04:50.790 --> 00:04:55.010
way--. One of the things, another word that
drives me crazy, aside from the death of TV,

00:04:55.010 --> 00:04:57.190
is that TV is a traditional medium.

00:04:57.190 --> 00:05:01.280
People say, "Oh, TV is traditional. Media
planners can handle that. We'll cover that

00:05:01.280 --> 00:05:06.140
in a meeting." And it's just not a traditional
medium anymore. It's not that simple. So,

00:05:06.140 --> 00:05:10.070
Mike and I look at it differently. We look
at it as a new medium. And as a new medium,

00:05:10.070 --> 00:05:14.041
we need to plan it differently than we've
planned it in the past.

00:05:14.041 --> 00:05:18.530
So, they way we talk about it with our clients
is there's three major shifts that we've seen

00:05:18.530 --> 00:05:22.790
happening. The first is that we have this
instant feedback loop, right? So, you put

00:05:22.790 --> 00:05:29.000
something out there and people have the ability
to respond instantaneously. They, we certainly

00:05:29.000 --> 00:05:33.570
do from a creative standpoint, we do tons
of pre-testing before we put creative on the

00:05:33.570 --> 00:05:34.570
air.

00:05:34.570 --> 00:05:39.040
We do tons of post-testing to see what's happening
and whether it's resonating with consumers.

00:05:39.040 --> 00:05:43.560
But you can also get this instant feedback
as soon as you put the creative on the air,

00:05:43.560 --> 00:05:46.510
