you might ask. Relationships do matter. I'm

00:27:33.549 --> 00:27:38.410
sure you hear this a lot, but I've been doing
this for over 20 years and the access that

00:27:38.410 --> 00:27:46.130
Mike and I got to people to understand their
vision of the media business was really important.

00:27:46.130 --> 00:27:50.809
And you get very different visions from different
people you talk to, from big media companies

00:27:50.809 --> 00:27:56.030
to small start-ups, and where they see their
place in this business. So, building those

00:27:56.030 --> 00:28:01.950
relationships over the years was really important.
Also, curiosity is important. So, one of the

00:28:01.950 --> 00:28:07.200
things--. I'm a, have been a television specialist
and Mike is a social media guy.

00:28:07.200 --> 00:28:13.110
That's his background. But the curiosity to
understand this business in a broader way,

00:28:13.110 --> 00:28:19.240
you need to have broader business knowledge.
You can't just know one thing anymore. But

00:28:19.240 --> 00:28:24.490
then, on the same token, one person can't
know everything, right? But you need to understand

00:28:24.490 --> 00:28:29.030
this business more broadly. And it's important
that the people you hire and the people that

00:28:29.030 --> 00:28:33.250
we hire at the agency, have the curiosity
and the desire to wanna know more.

00:28:33.250 --> 00:28:40.061
And you can't be territorial. This one is--.
Every time I talk to people about, "How are

00:28:40.061 --> 00:28:44.610
you and Mike working together?" Like, we have
so many struggles with TV and digital people

00:28:44.610 --> 00:28:50.770
working together. And you just can't be territorial.
The one thing I will say is Mike is one of

00:28:50.770 --> 00:28:55.330
the few digital people who've I met, who is
really passionate about TV.

00:28:55.330 --> 00:29:00.900
There's no chip on his shoulder that digital
is better than TV. And vice versa, that TV

00:29:00.900 --> 00:29:04.860
is better than digital. And we really need
to make sure we're forging these relationships,

00:29:04.860 --> 00:29:10.049
both at the agency side and on the media company's
side, that the groups are all working together.

00:29:10.049 --> 00:29:15.940
And we say it a lot and it's easy to say and
it makes total sense, but it actually happening

00:29:15.940 --> 00:29:17.910
is not easy.

00:29:17.910 --> 00:29:23.100
And I think the reason why Mike and I have
been successful in doing this over the last

00:29:23.100 --> 00:29:27.860
year or so, is because we just work really
well together and recognize that I couldn't

00:29:27.860 --> 00:29:31.800
have done this on my own and he couldn't have
done this on his own. But together, we were

00:29:31.800 --> 00:29:36.750
able to really create something that we think
adds value to our clients.

00:29:36.750 --> 00:29:38.200
[pause]

00:29:38.200 --> 00:29:42.530
Still a few challenges ahead. There's been
a lot of experimentation in this space over

00:29:42.530 --> 00:29:46.530
the last year. And there will continue to
be experimentation. Most of the experimentation

00:29:46.530 --> 00:29:50.480
is on the content creator side and what kind
of things should they be creating in this

00:29:50.480 --> 00:29:57.880
space. Some advertisers have come in and done
some interesting sponsorships of this content.

00:29:57.880 --> 00:30:01.299
And you'll think you'll see a little bit more
