So, I mean, I think YouTube is valuable as
a distribution for content--the YouTube channels

00:53:49.999 --> 00:53:56.850
and branded channels as a distribution for
the content we're creating. So, I mean, I

00:53:56.850 --> 00:54:00.509
think it's very valuable. Its obviously has
a tremendous reach.

00:54:00.509 --> 00:54:06.699
So, we need to make sure that we're using
it in the right way. I do think--not sure

00:54:06.699 --> 00:54:09.991
this quite answers your question--but I do
think, from a content standpoint, what they

00:54:09.991 --> 00:54:15.109
are doing now with creating content and trying
to compete with television programming is

00:54:15.109 --> 00:54:20.049
going to be interesting to watch to see if
people want to view programming and are willing

00:54:20.049 --> 00:54:25.119
to experiment and test out that programming
to gain some traction and some scale.

00:54:25.119 --> 00:54:31.940
So, YouTube's a valuable platform. I'm not
sure that quite answers your question, but

00:54:31.940 --> 00:54:32.940
next time we'll bring Mike.

00:54:32.940 --> 00:54:33.940
&gt;&gt;Female #4: Thanks.

